cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the effect of full-duplex cooperative relaying in a multiuser network, which involves aspects of networking, information theory, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves modeling and analysis of performance metrics, which suggests the possibility of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of multi-packet reception and the impact on throughput and delay may also relate to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
